		"details": {
			"description": "<p>A floating skull of fire swoops around the arena, rotating as it weaves through the ring and releasing huge gouts of flame in random directions.</p>",
			"disable": "<p>three @Check[thievery|dc:40|name:Disable an Elemental Core|traits:action:disable-a-device,hazard,magical,trap,fire] (Master) checks or castings of @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.9HpwDN4MYQJnW0LG]{Dispel Magic} (7th rank; counteract DC 40), one each to pull out or disable the elemental cores hidden in the floating skull's right eye, left eye, and mouth</p>",
			"isComplex": true,
			"level": {
				"value": 16
			},
			"publication": {
				"license": "OGL",
				"remaster": false,
				"title": "Pathfinder #167: Ready? Fight!",
				"authors": ""
			},
			"reset": "",
			"routine": "<p>(3 actions) The trap loses 1 action per turn per successful check to disable. The floating flamethrower uses its first action to release a gout of flame in a @Template[cone|distance:15] that deals @Damage[(3d12+18)[fire]] damage (@Check[reflex|dc:40|basic] save), its second action to fly in a U-shape in a random direction, and its third action to release another gout of flame.</p>"
		},
